cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper proposes a model for generating expressive orofacial movements based on speech input. This involves the use of articulatory and emotional features extracted from the speech signal as conditioning inputs. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Speech and Dialogue Processing (cs.SD), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Multimedia (cs.MM).
